<subSubSection pageId="15" pageNumber="2342" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="15.[160,1156,774,939]" box="[160,262,774,800]" pageId="15" pageNumber="2342">
<heading box="[160,262,774,800]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="15" pageNumber="2342" reason="5">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,262,774,800]" inLineHeading="true" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="2342" reason="3">Remarks</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="15.[160,1156,774,939]" pageId="15" pageNumber="2342">
The species is close to 
<taxonomicName authority="Kusigemati, 1971" authorityName="Kusigemati" authorityYear="1971" box="[429,854,810,835]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Exochus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="2342" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="convergens">
<emphasis box="[429,649,810,835]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="2342">Exochus convergens</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Kusigemati K" box="[659,854,811,835]" pageId="15" pageNumber="2342" pagination="205 - 298" refId="ref17244" refString="Kusigemati K. 1971. Taxonomic studies on the subfamiliy Metopiinae of Japan (Hymenoptera: ichneumonidae). Memoirs of the Faculty of Agric, Kagoshima Univ. 8: 205 - 298." type="journal article" year="1971">Kusigemati, 1971</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, but differs by its clypeus with straight apical margin, longer malar space, presence of occipital carina laterally, number of flagellomeres, shorter first flagellomere, presence of costula, shorter hind femur and coloration of the body.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
